values.description: or 0x8 = File name cannot contain the at symbol (@)
or 0x4 = File name cannot be empty
or 0x4000 = Detached drawing save as options is not supported
or 0x80 = Do not overwrite an existing file
or 0x100 = File name extension does not match the SOLIDWORKS document type
or 0x800 = File name cannot exceed 255 characters
or 0x200 = Save the selected bodies in a part document. Valid option for IPartDoc::SaveToFile2 ; however, not a valid option for IModelDocExtension::SaveAs

or 0x1000 = Save As operation: is not supported was executed is such a way that the resulting file might not be complete, possibly because SOLIDWORKS is hidden; if the error persists after setting SOLIDWORKS to visible and re-attempting the Save As operation, contact SOLIDWORKS API support .
or 0x20 = Save As file type is not valid
or 0x2000 = Saving an assembly with renamed components requires saving the references
